# Label2 for subdetail and descriptions

All **subdetail** and **description** text in list cells, section headers, and similar UI MUST use the **label2** font.

## Scope

- **Description**: Secondary or supporting copy (e.g. ListCell `description`, `descriptionNode`).
- **Subdetail**: Extra detail line (e.g. ListCell `subdetail`, `subdetailNode`).

## Implementation

- Use CDS `Text` with `font="label2"` for description and subdetail content.
- When passing a string to `description` or `subdetail`, the component may apply its own font; prefer `descriptionNode` / `subdetailNode` with explicit `<Text font="label2">` when you need to guarantee label2.
- Do not use `font="body"`, `font="label1"`, or other fonts for description or subdetail unless a design exception is documented.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — description and subdetail use label2
<ListCell
  title="Bitcoin"
  description={<Text as="span" font="label2" color="fgMuted">BTC</Text>}
  subdetailNode={
    <Text font="label2" display="block" textAlign="end" color="fgPositive">
      ↗ £3.12 (0.35%)
    </Text>
  }
/>

// ❌ BAD — description uses body or default
<ListCell description={<Text font="body">BTC</Text>} />
```
